00:38:53.323 --> 00:38:54.153
mean?
Professor Charles

00:38:54.153 --> 00:38:55.475
Bailyn: Okay.
So, imagine you're a

00:38:55.475 --> 00:38:58.409
one-dimensional creature.
You can only go on a line.

00:38:58.409 --> 00:39:00.481
But your line,
unbeknownst to you,

00:39:00.481 --> 00:39:02.930
is curved, so that it ends on
itself.

00:39:02.930 --> 00:39:07.190
That then--the line expands.
The circle expands.

00:39:07.190 --> 00:39:10.556
What do you think is happening?
You think suddenly all the

00:39:10.556 --> 00:39:13.131
distances are greater,
but you can't perceive what

00:39:13.131 --> 00:39:15.419
it's expanding into,
because that's a second

00:39:15.419 --> 00:39:18.000
dimension, and you're
constrained to move on the line.

00:39:18.000 --> 00:39:20.924
Similarly, if you're an ant,
or something moving on the

00:39:20.924 --> 00:39:23.883
surface of the Earth,
and you have no understanding

00:39:23.883 --> 00:39:26.659
that there's up and down,
and the Earth suddenly

00:39:26.659 --> 00:39:30.382
increases in size,
you have no perception of the

00:39:30.382 --> 00:39:34.005
dimension you're moving into.
Student: So then,

00:39:34.005 --> 00:39:36.030
they just keep moving into
higher dimensions?

00:39:36.030 --> 00:39:37.875
Professor Charles
Bailyn: Well,

00:39:37.875 --> 00:39:40.469
our perception is of a
three-dimensional Universe.

00:39:40.469 --> 00:39:44.298
So, if you say,
okay, what happens when the

00:39:44.298 --> 00:39:47.706
scale factor gets bigger?
You can write it down

00:39:47.706 --> 00:39:49.598
mathematically into all these
calculations,

00:39:49.598 --> 00:39:52.552
and what you have to imagine,
if you want to have a

00:39:52.552 --> 00:39:56.370
conceptual understanding of
this, is that there's some

00:39:56.370 --> 00:40:00.477
fourth spatial dimension into
which this three-dimensional

00:40:00.477 --> 00:40:03.739
space is moving into.
But we can't perceive that.

00:40:03.739 --> 00:40:06.113
So, it's better to do it
mathematically,

00:40:06.113 --> 00:40:09.277
because it's hard on the brain
to imagine that fourth

00:40:09.277 --> 00:40:11.818
dimension.
And there's basically two ways

00:40:11.818 --> 00:40:14.300
to think about this.
One is by analogy.

00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:16.204
You think of the
one-dimensional creature and

00:40:16.204 --> 00:40:18.110
what it thinks about the second
dimension,

00:40:18.110 --> 00:40:20.028
or the two-dimensional
creature--what it thinks about

00:40:20.028 --> 00:40:21.839
the third dimension.
And then, you just,

00:40:21.839 --> 00:40:24.733
sort of, take this leap of
faith into us moving into the

00:40:24.733 --> 00:40:26.511
fourth.
Or, you have to write things

00:40:26.511 --> 00:40:28.582
down mathematically.
Those are the only two options

00:40:28.582 --> 00:40:30.689
you have.
Actually picturing this is not

00:40:30.689 --> 00:40:33.039
going to happen.
Yes?

00:40:33.039 --> 00:40:36.732
Student: If we were to
speed up this process would we

00:40:36.732 --> 00:40:40.050
be able to see things getting
farther away from us?

00:40:40.050 --> 00:40:40.888
Professor Charles
Bailyn: Ah,

00:40:40.888 --> 00:40:43.182
interesting question.
Would we, if we cranked up this

00:40:43.182 --> 00:40:44.924
process some,
would we actually,

00:40:44.924 --> 00:40:48.353
you know, be able to take out
our tape measure and notice that

00:40:48.353 --> 00:40:51.670
the distance between here and
Starbucks has increased?

00:40:51.670 --> 00:40:53.869
No.
Here's why.

00:40:53.869 --> 00:40:57.826
We are not--we--that is to say,
you, me, our bodies,

00:40:57.826 --> 00:41:02.713
whatever--are not participating
in the expansion of the Universe

00:41:02.713 --> 00:41:05.070
at the moment.
Why?

00:41:05.070 --> 00:41:08.389
Because the molecules in our
body are being held together by

00:41:08.389 --> 00:41:12.530
other forces--chemical forces.
We are being--the Earth is held

00:41:12.530 --> 00:41:17.134
together by gravitational forces
and those forces have stopped

00:41:17.134 --> 00:41:20.230
the expansion of the Universe
locally,

00:41:20.230 --> 00:41:23.384
but not globally.
And that's why you have to go

00:41:23.384 --> 00:41:25.099
out and measure this stuff with
galaxies.

00:41:25.099 --> 00:41:30.010
Otherwise, you'd be able to,
you know, measure it with this.

00:41:30.010 --> 00:41:31.745
Now, of course,
then, there's the problem,

00:41:31.745 --> 00:41:33.820
the ruler also expands,
all this kind of stuff.

00:41:33.820 --> 00:41:36.958
But, in fact,
what happens is that

00:41:36.958 --> 00:41:40.667
locally--local objects,
by which I mean,

00:41:40.667 --> 00:41:45.993
our own galaxy and anything
smaller, are held together by

00:41:45.993 --> 00:41:49.310
other forces.
Picture a balloon expanding,

00:41:49.310 --> 00:41:52.440
so that's the two-dimensional
case, this balloon expands.

00:41:52.440 --> 00:41:55.329
And put a bunch of leather
patches on the balloon.

00:41:55.329 --> 00:41:58.644
So, those leather patches don't
expand, but the distance

00:41:58.644 --> 00:42:02.260
between--because they're held
together by something else--but

00:42:02.260 --> 00:42:05.610
the distance between them does.
Yes?

00:42:05.610 --> 00:42:07.510
Student: So,
what causes the expansion?

00:42:07.510 --> 00:42:09.182
Professor Charles
Bailyn: What causes the

00:42:09.182 --> 00:42:12.250
expansion?
Oh, that's theology.

00:42:12.250 --> 00:42:16.289
No, no, seriously,
it's an initial condition.

00:42:16.289 --> 00:42:22.970
Something at the start,
at T equals 0,

00:42:22.970 --> 00:42:28.701
where this A is 0.
So, you're starting with

00:42:28.701 --> 00:42:32.712
A of--with this scale
factor of 0, but the derivative

00:42:32.712 --> 00:42:34.263
isn't 0.
It's expanding,

00:42:34.263 --> 00:42:36.280
A is increasing.
Why?

00:42:36.280 --> 00:42:39.380
Why is it increasing by the
particular amount it is?

00:42:39.380 --> 00:42:43.069
You have to think of that as
being a parameter of the

00:42:43.069 --> 00:42:45.084
Universe.
It's one of the things about

00:42:45.084 --> 00:42:46.760
the--sort of like the speed of
light.

00:42:46.760 --> 00:42:50.790
Why is that the quantity it is?
Or why is the gravitational

00:42:50.790 --> 00:42:55.233
constant the value it is?
It's one of the parameters that

00:42:55.233 --> 00:42:59.989
governs our Universe.
Why those particular parameters?

00:42:59.989 --> 00:43:05.330
That's not quite a science
question, and we don't know.

00:43:05.330 --> 00:43:07.481
You can turn it around.
You can make the following

00:43:07.481 --> 00:43:09.620
interesting point.
If it wasn't expanding at

00:43:09.620 --> 00:43:13.054
approximately the rate it is,
we wouldn't be here to notice

00:43:13.054 --> 00:43:15.995
it.
Because if it was expanding a

00:43:15.995 --> 00:43:20.274
whole lot slower,
then it would never have gotten

00:43:20.274 --> 00:43:23.840
big enough for stars to condense
out.

00:43:23.840 --> 00:43:27.917
If it was expanding a whole lot
faster, all the atoms would be

00:43:27.917 --> 00:43:31.659
spread out so far that,
again, stars could never form.

00:43:31.659 --> 00:43:34.214
So, you can make this
interesting argument that while

00:43:34.214 --> 00:43:36.670
you don't know why it has this
particular value,

00:43:36.670 --> 00:43:39.837
it's very important that it
does, because otherwise we

00:43:39.837 --> 00:43:43.551
wouldn't be here to observe it.
This is a form of argumentation

00:43:43.551 --> 00:43:47.470
called the anthropic principle.
It is highly debated among

00:43:47.470 --> 00:43:52.120
scientists whether this is a
scientific argument or not.

00:43:52.120 --> 00:43:55.059
But it's amusing either way.
So--yes?

